# Component stories + tests

Hand-authored components in `src/app/components/` **must** ship with colocated `*.stories.tsx` that Vitest runs via Storybook play functions.

**Do not** add `test` tags or play tests to the generated Astryx catalog under `src/storybook/astryx/generated/` — that catalog is docs-only.

## Commands

```bash
vp run storybook          # browse catalog + Vibework stories
vp test                   # Vitest browser tests — app components only
vp check                  # format, lint, typecheck
```

First-time browser setup: `pnpm exec playwright install chromium`

## Scope

| Path | Storybook config | Vitest |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `src/app/components/**/*.stories.tsx` | `.storybook-vitest/main.ts` | Yes — `tags: ["test"]` |
| `src/storybook/astryx/**` | `.storybook/main.ts` | No |

Vitest uses `.storybook-vitest/` so the full catalog is never imported during `vp test`.

## Checklist for every new or changed component

1. Colocate `my-widget.stories.tsx` next to `my-widget.tsx`
2. Meta: `title: "Vibework/Components/MyWidget"`, `tags: ["autodocs", "test"]`
3. Every `export const …: Story` includes a `play` function
4. Import test utils from `storybook/test` (`expect`, `within`, `userEvent`, `fn` as needed) — not `@testing-library/*`
5. Run `vp test` and `vp check`

Copy patterns from `feature-card.stories.tsx` or `home-form.stories.tsx`.

**Play guidelines**

- Presentational: assert roles/text (`getByRole`, `getByText`)
- Interactive: `userEvent` + assert outcomes
- Callback props: `fn()` in meta `args`, `toHaveBeenCalledOnce()` in `play`

## Config (do not point Vitest at the full catalog)

- `vitest.config.ts` — `@storybook/addon-vitest` + Playwright browser
- `.storybook-vitest/main.ts` — glob: `src/app/components/**/*.stories.tsx` only
- `.storybook/main.ts` — full Storybook for local browsing

## Storybook MCP

Requires Storybook running: `vp run storybook` → MCP at `http://localhost:6006/mcp` (`.cursor/mcp.json`).

After story changes, run `vp test` — MCP complements but does not replace it.

**Installing addons:** `pnpm add -D @storybook/addon-…` + register in `.storybook/main.ts` — not `vpx storybook add` or `npm`.
